Solution 1: Suffix Array For each suffix starting from $i$, the length of the shortest unique substring which is a prefix of that suffix is $\max(lcp_i, lcp_{i+1})+1$ where $lcp_0$ and $lcp_{n}$ is defined to be $0$. Note that if that length is greater than the length of suffix, it&rsquo;s an invalid substring
